Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech in Indianapolis, Indiana, where he addressed the recent shooting at Santa Fe High School in Texas and expressed condolences to the victims and their families. He also discussed the actions taken by the Trump administration to improve school safety and prevent mass shootings. Pence then highlighted the achievements of the Trump administration, including tax cuts, job creation, and deregulation. He criticized Senator Joe Donnelly for voting against the tax cuts and urged the audience to spread the message of the administration's accomplishments. Pence concluded his speech by calling on the audience to pray for America and its people.